news.title: Swedish home prices slide again in July as economic gloom deepens
news.para: Home prices fell 2.9% month-on-month, figures from Valueguard's HOX Index showed, while prices were down 2.6% from the same month in 2021.

news.title: China probes state property firm executives for 'serious violations'
news.para: Authorities said in separate notices on Tuesday that they were investigating Zhuang Yuekai, chairman of C&D Real Estate, and Shi Zhen, chairman of C&D Urban Services.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body to auction 18 commercial properties
news.para: The civic body has estimated Rs 61.71 crore as reserve price for the properties, varying from over Rs 3 crore to Rs 6 crore for each as per size, location and other criteria.

news.title: Indore civic body seals nine commercial outlets
news.para: Three establishments of Bicholi Mardana area including two food outlets and an automobile service station were sealed for operating without completion certificates.

news.title: Mumbai: Three weak buildings around crashed Borivli house demolished
news.para: Gitanjali building, over four decades old, crashed on the afternoon of August 19 but fortunately nobody was injured as the residents had run out after feeling tremors.

news.title: Omkar Group promoters discharged in money laundering case
news.para: Earlier this month, the accused moved discharge pleas before the special PMLA court through their advocates Vijay Aggarwal and Rahul Agarwal.

news.title: Maharashtra housing federation fine with water data share, not fee
news.para: The federation would apprise the state government about it because most of the groundwater sources like borewells were dry and not being used, said Suhas Patwardhan, the vice-chairman of the Maharashtra State Housing Federation.

news.title: Supertech twin towers demolition: 'No fly zone' for drones in Noida on Aug 28
news.para: While all residents of two adjoining societies -- Emerald Court and ATS Village -- would be evacuated, an exclusion zone has been marked around the twin towers where no person, vehicle or animal would be allowed during the demolition process, the officials said.

news.title: SMSs for additional property tax sent inadvertently: Pune civic chief
news.para: Nearly 60,000 property owners across the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) limits had received such messages from the civic body.

news.title: High-rise Lucknow development body societies hit a new low with broken lifts
news.para: Residents said they were facing frequent breakdowns in elevator systems ever since they got possession of flats. Most of them claimed that parts used to make elevators are of substandard quality that leads to breakdowns.

news.title: Indore: Legal ownership of land set to be provided in 400 villages
news.para: In the remaining 321 villages, the administration is facing some technical issues or the same have been listed in the ‘abandoned’ category in the existing records.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Floor space index rate changed for properties along metro
news.para: All properties located 500m from central line of the metro rail corridor that is proposed, under construction or completed and for which administrative sanction has been accorded, the premium FSI will be charged 50% of the applicable premium FSI.

news.title: Over 80 structures in Pune rural not fit for habitation
news.para: With the Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) area spread across 7,000 sqkm, most of these structures are in rural areas and notices to evacuate them have been issued by the gram panchayats, said a senior PMRDA official.

news.title: Nagpur: Within a year, PMAY flats face rainwater seepage, cracks & various other problems
news.para: Under PMAY, NMRDA had constructed 942 flats on khasra no. 62 under mouza Tarodi. There are 48 wings with G+4 floors each. NMRDA had handed over possession of 450 flats, of which 320 are occupied.

news.title: Centre orders release of Rs 35.28 crore under PMAY-Gramin to Punjab
news.para: The directions came after Punjab Rural Development Minister Kuldeep Singh Dhaliwal brought to the knowledge of Patil the pending funds under the scheme, an official release issued here said.
